Release Notes:

The rise of Australian trio MIDNIGHT JUGGERNAUTS has been meteoric! After building a strong reputation from live shows and their first self titled EP, they released the massive "Secrets Of The Universe" EP in June 2006, which gave us two of the biggest tracks on Triple J and community radio last year: "45 & Rising" and "Shadows". Since then they have been touring the country and building a following that resulted in sold out shows everywhere they have played including The Metro (wall to wall dancing) in Sydney and The Prince in Melbourne just a few months ago
And now, the long awaited debut album is upon us: "Dystopia" Vincent, Andy & newest addition Dan (ex VALENTINOS) have delivered beyond expectations.
Their masterful blend of electro & indie with insanely catchy songwriting will make genres and comparisons irrelevant, their appeal is that broad
